Documentation for raw Ecosim data:

Obtained Anchovy Bay example model and time series CSV from textbook, as provided per download in the 'Time series fitting' tutorial.

Added mediation function for seals-mackerel-anchovy as described in the textbook's 'Mediation' tutorial.

Added three environmental (foraging) responses to bottom temperature for cod, whiting, and anchovy, as described in the textbook's 'Incorporating environmental forcing' tutorial.

Fit the model (vulnerabilities and primary production anomaly) to model data as in the textbook's 'Time series fitting' tutorial.

Note that this model serves for examples, teaching, experimentation, and testing; it hence includes some aspects that are ecologically unrealistic (e.g., the seals-mackerel-anchovy mediation function from the textbook, an interaction that was "invented""for demonstration purposes ).

The example data include 5 files:

"Anchovy Bay_Ecosim_ex.eiixml": The example model as described above.
"Anchovy Bay_Ecosim_ex.EwEmdb": The Ecosim model in the EwE software's database format (version 6.7.0, 32 bits).
"anchovy_bay_ecosim_timeseries.csv": Time series imported into the model.
"anchovy_bay_ecosim_output_cumulative.csv": Absolute biomass time series produced with a single run of the model.
"anchovy_bay_ecosim_output_relative_biomass.csv": Relative biomass time series produced with a single run of the model.

The example model and data were obtained from the online textbook in April 2026. The textbook is available at https://pressbooks.bccampus.ca/ewemodel/. The model and data remain the intellectual property of the textbook's authors. We kindly thank Villy Christensen for the permission to include them in the package.
